tspan.tspan: The Drug and Health Product Register
Cyclops High Level Architechture and Flow Diagram

text.tspan: Stats Canada developers access Health Canada
Network and HC Cloud network through secure
VPN tunnel (thick or thin client), via whitelisted
locations. Health Canada developers will access
the VPN directly from the HC network.
While connected to the VPN service, Stats Canada
developers access the management jumpbox
through SSH.
From the management jumpbox, Stats Canada
developers will then be able to SSH through the
perimeter firewall to access the Cyclops virtual
machines and other resources.
The primary resource is a Virtual Machine
(Standard_B4ms). This VM will be allocated a
256GB premium SSD each as well being deployed
on their own subnets.
This VM will be a development sandbox running
Red Hat Enterprise Linux. Technologies running on
the VMs include Docker, Anaconda, Python and a
front end web stack.
The VM will be required to make outgoing
calls through the perimeter firewall to several
external APIs and services.
The VMs will need to make outgoing calls to the
Drug and Health Product register application.
The VMs will need to make outgoing calls to the
Licenced Natural Health Product Database API.
The VMs will need to make outgoing calls to the
public github (www.github.com) to syncronize
version control. Developers will also access
this version control from their environments.
ROEB inspectors will be required to access the
application, while field testing, through the
internet.( )
